  "prompt": "What is the relation between frequency and time period?",
  "response": "The relation between frequency and time period is that they are reciprocals of each other. Here's a detailed explanation:\n\n1. Mathematical Relationship:\nFrequency (f) = 1 / Time Period (T)\nTime Period (T) = 1 / Frequency (f)\n\n2. Units:\n- Frequency is measured in Hertz (Hz), which represents cycles per second\n- Time period is measured in seconds (s)\n\n3. Example:\n- If frequency is 2 Hz, time period is 1/2 = 0.5 seconds\n- If time period is 0.25 seconds, frequency is 1/0.25 = 4 Hz\n\n4. Key Points:\n- As frequency increases, time period decreases\n- As time period increases, frequency decreases\n- They have an inverse (reciprocal) relationship\n\n5. Formula:\nf = 1/T\nT = 1/f\n\nThis relationship is fundamental in physics, particularly in waves, oscillations, and periodic phenomena like sound, light, and electromagnetic waves.",
